<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Html5 on Learn, Converse, Share</title><link>http://jmeridth.com/tags/html5/</link><description>Recent content in Html5 on Learn, Converse, Share</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 31 Mar 2013 00:00:00 -0500</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://jmeridth.com/tags/html5/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Fix Rendering With Presence of Doctype</title><link>http://jmeridth.com/posts/fix-rendering-with-presence-of-doctype/</link><pubDate>Sun, 31 Mar 2013 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate><guid>http://jmeridth.com/posts/fix-rendering-with-presence-of-doctype/</guid><description>&lt;p>A couple times now I’ve forgotten to render the DOCTYPE in my layouts on my web apps. The DOCTYPE element tells the browser what type of file to expect. It needs to be the first line in your document, so it usually goes in your application layout file.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In HTML or ERB:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="cp">&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>In &lt;a href="http://haml.info" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HAML&lt;/a>:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">!!! 5
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>Other &lt;a href="http://haml.info/docs/yardoc/file.REFERENCE.html#doctype_" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HAML Doctypes&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The above is the format for HTML 5. I don’t bother with the &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_doctype.asp" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HTML 4.01 DOCTYPEs&lt;/a>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>